Gauteng police have launched an investigation after four  bodies, suspected to be of illegal miners, were found on the side of the road in Benoni on Tuesday night. Police spokesperson Lt-Col Mavela Masondo said police  opened an inquest docket  after the bodies were found at about 8.15pm. A postmortem will be conducted to confirm the cause of death. “The deceased are suspected to be illegal miners.” Masondo said the police received an anonymous call about the bodies  left next to the road. “On arrival, police found four bodies  wrapped in blankets and plastic,” he said. The bodies have not yet been identified. TimesLIVE 